# Design System Tokens

NEVER use hardcoded colors, spacing, or radii. Always use CSS variables from `:root` in `src/styles/global.css`.

## Colors

- Backgrounds: `--bg-primary`, `--bg-secondary`, `--bg-tertiary`, `--bg-surface`, `--bg-elevated`, `--bg-hover`, `--bg-active`, `--bg-header`, `--bg-selected`
- Text: `--text-primary`, `--text-secondary`, `--text-muted`, `--text-inverse`
- Borders: `--border`, `--border-subtle`, `--border-focus`
- Accent: `--accent`, `--accent-hover`, `--accent-muted`, `--accent-soft`
- Semantic: `--success`, `--error`, `--warning`, `--info`, `--purple`
- Button text on accent/error backgrounds: use `var(--text-inverse)`, NOT `#fff`

## Spacing (gutter tokens)

| Token | Value | Use |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `--gutter-xs` | 4px | Tight gaps between small elements |
| `--gutter-sm` | 8px | Standard small gap, compact padding |
| `--gutter` | 14px | Default padding, standard gap |
| `--gutter-lg` | 18px | Toolbar/panel padding, button padding |

NEVER use magic numbers like `18px`, `14px`, `8px` for padding/margin/gap. Use gutter tokens.

## Border Radius

| Token | Value | Use |
|-------|-------|-----|
| `--radius-xs` | 3px | Tags, badges, small pills |
| `--radius-sm` | 5px | Buttons inside containers, chips |
| `--radius-md` | 8px | Inputs, buttons, cards |
| `--radius-lg` | 12px | Dialogs, panels, scrollbar thumbs |
| `--radius-xl` | 16px | Large modals, overlays |

NEVER use raw `3px`, `4px`, `10px`, `12px`. Use the tokens.

## Element Heights

Three standardized tiers:
- **Compact (28px)**: search inputs, small icon buttons, filter controls
- **Standard (34px)**: tree nodes, tab items, ghost buttons, secondary inputs
- **Full (38px)**: primary inputs, main buttons

## Shadows

`--shadow-sm`, `--shadow-md`, `--shadow-lg`, `--shadow-dropdown`

## Dark Mode Font Weight

WebKitGTK (Tauri on Linux) adds ~100 to font-weight. Dark mode uses `font-weight: 300` globally and `font-weight: 200` on `.grid-table` to compensate. Do NOT override these.
